# Phase 2 -- MCP Server + EVA Integrations

---

## Feature: MCP Server [ID=EO-07]

Expose all eva-veritas capabilities as MCP tools so any agent in the EVA ecosystem (or external) can invoke them.
Host in **29-foundry** alongside existing MCP servers.

### Story: Implement MCP server entrypoint [ID=EO-07-001] [IMPL]

`src/mcp-server.js` -- HTTP server exposing MCP-compatible JSON tool definitions.
Tool manifest endpoint: `GET /tools`.
Tool invoke endpoint: `POST /tools/{name}`.

### Story: Implement audit_repo MCP tool [ID=EO-07-002] [IMPL]

Inputs: `repo_path` (string).
Runs discover + reconcile internally.
Returns: `{ gaps[], coverage{}, trust_score, actions[] }`.
No filesystem side effects in MCP mode (in-memory only).

### Story: Implement get_trust_score MCP tool [ID=EO-07-003] [IMPL]

Inputs: `repo_path`.
Returns: `{ score, components{}, actions[] }`.
Runs full pipeline if `.eva/trust.json` is stale or absent.

### Story: Implement get_coverage MCP tool [ID=EO-07-004] [IMPL]

Inputs: `repo_path`.
Returns: `{ stories_total, stories_with_artifacts, stories_with_evidence, consistency_score }`.

### Story: Implement generate_ado_items MCP tool [ID=EO-07-005] [IMPL]

Inputs: `repo_path`, optional `include_gaps` (bool, default true).
Returns: structured array of work items (Epic / Feature / Story) with gap tags.

### Story: Implement scan_portfolio MCP tool [ID=EO-07-006] [IMPL]

Inputs: `portfolio_root` (e.g. `C:\AICOE\eva-foundation`), optional `project_filter[]`.
Runs `audit_repo` for each numbered project folder.
Returns: `{ projects: [{ id, name, trust_score, gap_count }], portfolio_mti }`.

