## Feature: Model Fidelity Audit [ID=EO-12]

Cross-reference declared data model entities (endpoints, screens, services, containers)
against what actually exists in the repository. Detects drift between the 37-data-model
API declarations and real filesystem/code evidence.

### Story: Implement model-audit command [ID=EO-12-001] [IMPL]

`eva model-audit [--repo <path>] [--data-model <url>] [--warn-only]`
`src/model-audit.js` — checks:
  - Screen `repo_path` -> file exists on disk
  - Endpoint `status=implemented` -> router file references the path
  - Service `is_active=true` -> docker-compose / Dockerfile reference
  - Container `fields[]` -> schema file covers >= 50% of declared fields
Writes `.eva/model-fidelity.json`. Exits code 1 if drift detected (unless --warn-only).